					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on Deuteronomy - a compilation of works of various authors.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="161v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Deuteronomy</title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>The commentary have been compiled and abridged from the works of several Karaite authors, including Abu Yusuf Ya῾ḳub al-Ḳirḳisani, al-Mu῾alim Abu ῾Ali, Al-Shaikh Abu Sari, Al-Shaikh Abu al-Faraj Harun, Abu al-Faraj Furḳan, al-Muḳadasi, and others.</p>
								<p>The codex from which this modern copy was made was accordingly finished in the first decade of Nisan, <date calendar="AM">1663</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1332</date>).</p>
								<p>Quotes several Karaite grammarians and other authorities.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
